creator: Macarius
description:
LibriVox recording of Fifty Spiritual Homiles of St Macarius the Egyptian by Macarius. (Translated by Arthur James Mason.)
Read in English by A LibriVox Volunteer
Macarius the Great of Egypt (c. 300 – 391) was one of the Desert Fathers of early Christian history. A wealth of wisdom and joy can be found in these homilies. (Summary by the Reader.)
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
